  author={Han Qing Ding and Jing Zhu},
  abstract={Drawing on the theory of frontstage–backstage and ethnomethodology, this study uses online ethnography and participatory observation to explore how norms are performed and constructed in Baidu Baike’s literary editing community. The backstage is divided into a “middle stage” for power negotiation and a “deep backstage” for building intimacy. These distinct interaction goals give rise to different types of norms, shaped by both platform rules and members’ tacit normative awareness. Norms are constructed through performative cues, role modeling by opinion leaders, and repeated feedback. The findings reveal a dynamic tension between norm construction and deconstruction, which continuously drives collaborative production on the platform.},
