  author={Nian Liu and Jing Zhu},
  abstract={Following the “RYB Kindergarten child abuse incident,” a surge of public anger erupted on Weibo. Using machine learning–based emotion recognition and social network analysis, this study examines key nodes in the spread of anger from three perspectives: node roles, actor types, and mechanisms of influence. The anger diffusion network exhibits a radial structure, with a few users in dominant positions. News media and celebrities serve as emotional initiators with high attraction power, while grassroots influencers act as emotional hubs with strong cohesion. Together, their interactions shift the flow of online discourse from facts and opinions toward emotions, shaping a multi-actor emotional landscape in online public opinion.},
